 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Destruction Warlock Phase 2 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 309 top-ranked Destruction Warlock DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 2 (Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Destruction Warlock items in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Belt of Blasting (92%), Voidheart Mantle (86%), Boots of Blasting (80%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Destruction Warlock use in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Chaotic Skyfire Diamond in the meta socket, then Veiled Noble Topaz, Glowing Nightseye and Runed Living Ruby in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Destruction Warlock need in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "10 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Power on head, Greater Inscription of Discipline on shoulders, Runic Spellthread on legs and Enchant Weapon - Sunfire on main hand. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Power comes from Almaador — Shattrath City."
  }
